data.enText: written or said at the beginning of sth as an introduction to what follows
intended as an introduction to a subject or an activity for people who have never done it before
offered for a short time only, when a product is first on sale
a special introductory price of just $10

data.chText: 本试销优惠只为期三天。
data.enText: This introductory offer is for three days only.

tr: serving as an introduction or preface

example: began the slide show with some introductory remarks

tr: serving as a base or starting point

value.def: An introductory remark, talk, or part of a book gives a small amount of general information about a particular subject, often before a more detailed explanation.

example.ex: ...an introductory course in religion and theology.

value.tran: 引言的;导论的;介绍性的

value.def: An introductory offer or price on a new product is something such as a free gift or a low price that is meant to attract new customers.

example.ex: ...just out on the shelves at an introductory price of £2.99.
example.tran: 刚刚以2.99英镑的新品促销价上架
